OpenBSD Lua Library

Implements:

 o pledge()
 o arc4random()
 o arc4random_uniform()

Works and has been tested on Lua 5.1, 5.2 and 5.3.

Note that pledge() (on the 19th January of 2016) will fail if you
give it a list of paths as the second parameter:

 -- OK
 o.pledge('rpath stdio')
 -- Error
 o.pledge('rpath stdio', {})

Build:

 $ mkdir build && cd build
 $ cmake .. -DMODLUA_VERSION=5.1
 $ make
 $ make install

Usage:

 #!/usr/bin/env lua51

 o = require('openbsd')
 ret, error_string = o.pledge('rpath stdio')
 if ret == -1 then
    error(error_string)
 end

Or:

 #!/usr/bin/env lua51

 o = require('openbsd')

 for i = 1, 10 do
     print(o.arc4random_uniform(20))
 end

